	     Cairo - Two accidents on Egypt's roads have killed at least 26 people in three days, authorities said. A collision on Saturday involving a minibus on a desert road 145km south of Cairo left 13 dead, the health ministry said. That came just days after a crash on the same road also claimed 13 lives. Accidents on Egypt's roads killed more than 5 000 people in 2016, according to official figures, and authorities have moved to strengthen enforcement of traffic laws. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  